{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The incident was sort of inconsequential, I thought, because children being children, you felt, well, you know, there's nothing major significance to this kind of incident.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My parents, I know, were very disturbed, and they were very unhappy that the first day would be so quickly ruined with unpleasantness.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went to school from 1934 to about 1936, to the same school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A lot things have changed, of course, in Germany in those intervening years, especially with the announcement of the Nuremberg Laws, where all the civil rights and all the privileges had been taken away from Jews.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And our life became very constrained, meaning that it was very obvious, the things you could, or most important, could not do.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You could not attend any public facilities, whether it be sports stadium, movies, opera, concert.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Everything was being strictly prohibited by signs appearing on the buildings, on the theater, saying Jews are prohibited from entering.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My own personal experience was, I had seen, until I was well past the age of 18, one single, solitary movie, which was the last chance my parents had to take me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it turned out to be-- I've forgotten the name, but a Shirley Temple movie.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that was sort of a very, you might say, significant and obvious restraint that I had to put up with because children like to go to movies.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And here, one of those pleasant things that each child is looking forward to could not be attended by me or my parents.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Schooling itself became now very erratic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Many things happened, which I won't necessarily go into all these details.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
